or:#C00000\"><br></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"color:#C00000\"><br></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"color:#C00000\"><br></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"color:#C00000\"><br></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"color:#C00000\"><br></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"color:#C00000\"><br></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"color:#C00000\"><br></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"color:#C00000\"><br></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"color:#C00000\"><br></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"color:#C00000\"><br></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"color:#C00000\"><br></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"color:#C00000\"><br></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"color:#C00000\"><br></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"color:#C00000\"><br></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"color:#C00000\"><br></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"color:#C00000\">EXECUTIVE SUMMARY <o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\nline-height:107%;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Maize, Zea mays L. (corn),\nis one of the most abundantly planted cereals in the world, and it is widely\nconsumed by millions of Nigerians as a staple food.&nbsp; It is also used for the production of animal\nfeeds, ethanol, sweeteners, oil and other related products.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;line-height:107%;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Maize is an important\ncereal crop in Sub-Saharan Africa, serving as an important staple food for more\nthan one billion people in the region. More than 300 million Africans depend on\nmaize as their main staple food crop. All parts of the crop can be used for\nfood and non-food products. Maize accounts for 30−50% of low-income household\nexpenditures in Africa. </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Global production of maize\nhas averaged approximately 1,000 million metric tonnes over the past decades.\nWith total production of about 11 MMT, Nigeria is arguably Africa’s second\nlargest producer of maize after South Africa. Ethiopia occupies the thirdplace\non the chart of largest producers of maize in Africa.&nbsp; These countries accounted for about 39% of\nthe continent’s total maize output in 2019. In Nigeria, the top ten maize\nproducing states are Borno, Niger, Plateau, Katsina, Gombe, Bauchi, Kogi,\nKaduna, Oyo and Taraba; these account for nearly two-thirds (64%) of the maize\nproduced in the country.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">About 45.5% of maize\nproduced in Nigeria is used to manufacture animal feeds and nearly 98% of all\nanimal feeds produced in Nigeria are used by poultry farmers. Maize accounts\nfor 60-65% of poultry feeds constituents. Further, 6.5% of maize produced in\nNigeria is used by brewing industries while 13% is used for the manufacturing\nof industrial flours, corn flakes and other confectionaries. The share of\nhousehold consumption of maize however stands at 10-15%. Despite being the\nsecond largest maize producer in Africa, Nigeria’s export capacity for the\nagricultural product is terribly low when equated with peers like South Africa\nwhich account for nearly two-third of maize export in the continent. </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">The relatively low maize\nexport in Nigeria is primarily due to several factors including poor maize\nyield and existence of an official ban on export. Maize yield in Nigeria stands\nat less than two (2) tonnes per hectare relative to 4.9 tonnes per hectare and\n4.2 tonnes per hectare in South Africa and Ethiopia respectively. This is due\nto continued usage of open pollinated variety (OPV) rather than improved hybrid\nseeds by the country’s maize farmers. As a result, production is low and can\nbarely satisfy the huge maize demand within Nigeria itself, estimated at 12 –\n15 MMT, thereby creating a maize supply gap of about 4 million metric tons\nannually. The supply gap necessitated the declaration of the export ban on\nmaize.&nbsp;&nbsp; According to the USDA, maize\nimports into Nigeria doubled from 500,000 metric tonnes to 1 million metric\ntonnes between October 2019 and October 2020, with implications for Nigeria’s\nNaira, GDP, exchange rate, level of inflation, interest rates and job creation.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\nline-height:107%;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Although, data published by\nthe USDA shows that Nigeria produced 11.6 million metric tons of maize in 2021,\nthe highest quantity made in the last six decades. </span><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:0in;margin-top:0in;\nmso-margin-bottom-alt:8.0pt;mso-margin-top-alt:0in;mso-add-space:auto;\ntext-align:justify;line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">The figure, when compared to the 10 million\nmetric tons recorded in 2020, shows a mere 16 per cent increase.</span><span style=\"font-size:18.0pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"color:black;mso-color-alt:windowtext\"><br>\n</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">If\nyou follow closely what is happening with maize farming in Nigeria, you will\nrealize that the industry is experiencing decline and falling from historic\nheights due to insecurity and banditry in the top ten major producers of maize\nfarming in Nigeria.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Decapolis has taken the\ninitiative to Pioneer maize farming in a new terrain devoid of banditry,\npastoralist conflict and over cultivated lands, furthermore, the location gives\nan opportunity to study new fauna and explore the social engineering of a new\nsociety where scholarly inducement and modern technology can make a huge\ndifference.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#C00000\">WHY DECAPOLIS AND MAIZE<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">The Maize Farming Industry\nis indeed a very large industry and is thriving in almost all parts of the\nworld, especially in developed countries with high tonnage per annum, such as\nthe United States of America (347MMT), China (261MMT), Brazil (101.1MMT), Argentina\n(56.9MMT), Ukraine (38.9.MMT), Indonesia (30.7MMT), India (27.7MMT), Mexico\n(27.2MMT), Romania (17.4MMT), and Russia (14.3MMT). As a result, fewer, yet\nlarger farms emerge across the industry. </span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-color-alt:windowtext\">Nigeria food security\nsituation depends largely on her ability to have 60% of her maize demand met,\nfor protein-based items; eggs, broiler meat, cattle and fish to be at a stable\nprice, maize farming should be pursued aggressively while the security\nchallenges linger, this will be an uphill task.&nbsp;\n</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-color-alt:windowtext\">One thing is certain\nwhen it comes to commercial maize farming, Decapolis conducted her market\nresearch and feasibility studies before choosing our current farm location for\nthe commencement of our maize project in 2021 and we have been able to\nestablish a value chain for our produce.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:black;mso-color-alt:windowtext\">Our long-term goal is to\nnot only cultivate maize and sell it for consumption in farm markets and to\nretailers and consumers but to start a complimentary business, as well, by\nbuilding a maize processing plant to&nbsp;process and package our maize,\nallowing us to contribute our quota to the global food security index that has\nbeen deteriorating, and thus threatening global food security, and more so to\nlift impoverished communities out of poverty, through provision of basic\namenities.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#C00000\">FARM LOCATIONS<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-color-alt:windowtext\">Decapolis Maize Farms is a farming outlet of\nDecapolis Multi Concept Limited. The pilot farm is located in Ika District,\nEnjema Ward 4, Ankpa Local Government Area of Kogi State (7°36\'25.9\"N\n7°40\'54.4\"E). We have 20-hectares farming operations, we have done\ndetailed market research and feasibility studies, and we have been able to\nsecure a well–situated and suitable 500-hectare plot of farmland to commence\nour large-scale commercial maize farming project at Abejukolo-Bagana Road,\nOmala Local Government Area in Kogi state, Nigeria.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-color-alt:windowtext\">Our commercial maize farm project is a standard farm;\nhence it will be involved in commercial maize cultivation, maize processing and\npackaging. We will be involved in both organic commercial maize farming and\nnon–organic commercial maize farming. We have put plans in place that will help\nus launch a standard and world–class maize processing plant within the first\nthree years of officially running Decapolis Maize Farms project. We will\nprocess and package maize and ensure that they flood the market both in Nigeria\nand in other countries of the world.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">We will compete with the best in the industry, which is\nwhy we&nbsp;have secured 500 hectares of farm land and have plans to secure\nmore, in due time, along with purchasing some farming equipment and\nmachinery.&nbsp; Additionally, we have hired\nsome key employees who are currently undergoing training so as to fit into the\nideal picture of the 21</span><sup><span style=\"font-size:8.5pt;font-family:\n&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">st</span></sup><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">&nbsp;century commercial maize farm workforce that we\nwant to build.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:#C00000\">OUR\nCONTRIBUTION<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Since inception, Decapolis has engaged over 250 widows,\n150 vulnerable children in harvesting where they are paid and fed daily, we\nhave 50 married women permanently on our work schedule, more so, we provide\nfull antenatal care (ANC) for over 5 women and counting, supported primary\nschool education for 20 children, supported vigilantes in our location with\nlogistics, communication equipment, training for youths on modern farm\nimplement handling, sprayers, planters, chemical measurements, weather study,\nsoil test and analysis, accounting and business classes. We hope to have a\nmultiplier effect in no time.&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">We are in the commercial maize farming business because\nwe want to leverage on the vast opportunities available in the commercial\nfarming industry to contribute our quota in growing the Nigerian economy, in\nnational food production, global food security, and in raw materials production\nfor industries. Exporting agricultural products from Nigeria to other countries\nout of our large-scale maize production will help to substantially reduce the\ndomestic demand gap while generating surplus for the export market and, over\nand above all, to make a profit. We will also serve as a research center for\nschools and colleges, as this will encourage agricultural entrepreneurships in\nNigerian schools. <o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Cooperate\nSocial Responsibilities (CRS) <o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">As a cooperate organization, we understand the importance\nof cooperate social responsibilities, hence the need for us to carry out health\ncare access initiatives in the pilot project locale, such as malaria treatment\nand prevention, deworming for school age children, and registering the most\nvulnerable women for antenatal care through partnership with the local health\ncenter in the same location.&nbsp; Moreso, we\nhave embarked on a project entitled “<b>Light up Ika</b>” a project in an\nimpoverished community that lights up one (1) household at a time, using solar\nenergy.&nbsp; Our long-term goal is to light\nup an entire community within our project communities. Furthermore, in our\ncurrent project location, we discovered that, we have over three hundred and\nthirty-eight (338) widows in just two of the nine communities there, hence the\nneed for us to ensure that at least 40% our manual labourers are widows, thus\nenabling them to support themselves and their children.&nbsp; Additionally, we offer educational\nscholarships for qualifying orphans. We also have a quarterly agricultural\nextension training classes in the same locality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Decapolis Maize Farms, is well positioned to become one\nof the leading commercial maize farms in Nigeria, which is why we have been\nable to source for the best hands, and why we are working so diligently on\npurchasing more farm machinery with which to run the farm. We have put\nprocesses and strategies in place that will help us employ best practices when\nit comes to commercial maize farming as required by the regulating bodies in\nNigeria.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#C00000\">OUR PRODUCTS AND SERVICES <o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Decapolis Maize Farms, is a commercial farm that is\ncommitted to cultivating both organic and non – organic maize for both the\nNigerian market and global market. We are in business to produce both food and\nraw materials for individuals and industries in commercial quantities. We will\nalso ensure that we operate a standard maize processing and packaging plant as\npart of our complementary services.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">We are in this line of business to make profits, and we\nwill ensure that we do all that is allowed by the law of Nigeria to achieve our\nbusiness goals and objectives. These are the areas we will concentrate on in\nour commercial maize farms:<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Cultivation of variety of maize (organic and\nnon – organic)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Standard Food Processing Plant<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">When the need arises, we will expand our efforts by\ncultivating related crops:<o:p></o:p></span></p><ul type=\"disc\">\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\">Rice<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\">Soy\n     beans<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\">Wheat\n     <strong><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><o:p></o:p></span></strong></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\">Cassava<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n</ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Our Mission and Vision Statement</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><ul type=\"disc\">\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\">Our\n     vision is to become one of the leading commercial maize farms and maize\n     processing and packing brands, not just in Nigeria, but also on the global\n     stage.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\">Decapolis\n     Maize Farms, is a world-class commercial maize farm that is in business to\n     cultivate organic,&nbsp;non – organic, and processed maize for both the\n     Nigerian market and international market, Decapolis is Farming to lift impoverished\n     communities out of poverty. <o:p></o:p></span></li>\n</ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\n&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Decapolis will\ncontribute her quota in growing the Nigerian economy, in national food\nproduction, in global food security, in raw materials production for\nindustries, and in exporting agricultural produce from Nigeria to other\ncountries<o:p></o:p></span></p><p><b style=\"text-align: justify; background-color: var(--form-control-bg); color: var(--default-font-color); font-size: 0.935rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#C00000\">OUR BUSINESS STRUCTURE</span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:\n11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Decapolis\nMaize Farms, is a commercial maize farm that started small in Kogi State, but\nhopes to grow much larger, in order to compete favorably with leading\ncommercial maize farms in the commercial farming industry both in Nigeria and\non the global stage.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">We are aware of the importance of building a solid\nbusiness structure that can support the vision of the kind of world-class\nbusiness we want to own. For this reason,&nbsp;Decapolis is committed to only\nhiring the best hands.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">At Decapolis Maize Farms, we will ensure that we hire\npeople that are qualified, hardworking, dedicated, customer-centric, and ready\nto work to help us build a prosperous business that will benefit all the\nstakeholders (the owners, partners, workforce, and customers).<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:\n11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">In\nview of the above, we have decided to hire qualified and competent hands to\noccupy the following positions at the moment;<o:p></o:p></span></p><ul type=\"disc\">\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\n     font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\">Team lead<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\n     font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\">Project Lead<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\n     font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\">General Farm Manager<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\n     font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\">Administrator/Accountant<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\n     font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\">Sales/Logistics Manager <o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\n     font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\">Field Employees<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\">Front Desk\n     Officer<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n</ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Local contributors <o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">o<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Chief of Enjema Ward 4, Ika District, Kogi\nState<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">o<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Vigilante Area Commander.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">o<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Youth Leader.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">o<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Women leader. <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">o<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Primary School Headteacher. <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Courier New&quot;;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">o<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Hospital Director.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 7.5pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#C00000\">SWOT ANALYSIS <o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Decapolis Maize Farms, does not intend to launch on a\ntrial-and-error basis, hence the need to conduct a proper SWOT analysis. We\nknow that if we get it right from the onset, we will have succeeded in creating\nthe foundation that will help us build a standard maize farm that will\nfavorably compete with leading commercial maize farms in Nigeria and\nother&nbsp;parts of the world.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">We are quite aware that there are several large,\nmedium,&nbsp;and small-scale maize farms all over Nigeria.&nbsp; However, during our feasibility studies, we\ndiscovered that the location of our maize farm project gave us an edge as it\nwas relatively free from the threats of banditry and herders invasion, unlike\nour experience at the trial one-acre maize farm project in Abuja that was\nravaged by herdsmen invasion. Further findings from the upper Northern states\nof Nigeria, who are key players in the maize farm industry, shows that, there\nhas been an invasion of herdsmen and bandits, thereby reducing their\ncontribution to the Nigerian metric tonnage output and affecting global food\nsecurity index.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">We know that if a proper SWOT analysis is conducted for\nour business, we will be able to position our business to maximize our\nstrength, leverage on the opportunities that will be available to us, mitigate\nour risks, and be equipped to confront our threats.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Decapolis Maize Farms, employed the services of an expert\nBusiness Analyst with bias in the commercial farming industry to help us\nconduct a thorough SWOT analysis and to help us&nbsp;create a business model\nthat will help us achieve our business goals and objectives.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:\n&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Here is a summary from\nthe result of the SWOT analysis that was conducted on behalf of Decapolis Maize\nFarm Project.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Strength<o:p></o:p></span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Our strength as a commercial maize farm is in the fact\nthat we have healthy relationships with many of the major players throughout\nthe chain of industry, including agricultural merchants who deal in maize in\nthe commercial farms industry both suppliers and buyers within and outside our\ncurrent farm location.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">We have used modern land preparation equipment, plough\nand harrow, seed planters, fertilizer applicators, sprayers, we have also\npartnered with Pioneer seeds and received technical and consultative supports\non daily and weekly basis, through video calls and all our part time and\nfull-time team have had at least 2 weeks intensive training on equipment and\nchemical handling.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">For the past two years, we have not had any incident of\nbanditry or herders’ invasion within the proximities of our farm locations,\nunlike when we did the trial one-acre maize project in Abuja (Federal Capital\nTerritory), where the entire crop was consumed by Fulani cattle just before\nharvest time.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">We are working toward buying some of the latest\ncommercial farming machines, tools and maize processing equipment that will\nhelp us cultivate maize in commercial quantities with less stress. Apart from\nour relationships (network) and this equipment, we can confidently boast that\nwe have some of the most experienced hands on our team.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Weakness<o:p></o:p></span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Our weakness could be that we are a new commercial maize\nfarm in Nigeria.&nbsp; The fact that we\ndecided to upscale from 20ha to 500ha and diversify our farming activities\ncould count against us, initially. We are aware of this and from our\nprojection, we will overcome this weakness with time and turn it into a major\nadvantage for the business.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Opportunities</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">The opportunities that are available to us\ncannot be quantified; we know that there are billions of individuals who\nconsume both organic and non – organic maize in different forms both in Nigeria\nand other parts of the world. We will ensure that we maximize the opportunities\navailable to commercial maize farmers. We know that the local and global demand\nfor maize is anticipated to keep growing as renewable energy targets rise each\nyear.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">We have already started to get request for\nmaize supply from major maize users within poultry industry in the Federal\nCapital Territory, Abuja;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Dahmos Agroallied&nbsp; (10,000 layers Farm)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Salbari Ranches (500 Dairy Cattle)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Mainland Farm (22,000 layers farm)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Ramispro (25,000 broilers a year farm)&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">The above four concerns can comfortably\nconsume 2500Tonnes of maize a year making our 500hectares project look like\nchild’s play.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Threat<o:p></o:p></span></strong></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Some of the threats and challenges that we\nare likely going to face when we upscale our commercial maize farm from the\ncurrent 20ha to 500ha or more, are a global economic downturn that can impact\nnegatively on household spending, bad weather conditions, natural disasters\n(draughts, epidemics),&nbsp;unfavorable government policies&nbsp;and the\narrival of &nbsp;more competitors.</span><span style=\"color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\"><br>\n</span><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">There is hardly anything one can do as\nregards these threats and challenges other than to be optimistic that things\nwill continue to work for our good.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>&nbsp;</b><b style=\"background-color: var(--form-control-bg); color: var(--default-font-color); font-size: 0.935rem;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:#C00000\">MARKET TRENDS</span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">One of the\ncommon trends in the commercial line of maize farming is that most players in\nthe industry are no longer concentrating only on non – organic maize farming.\nFarmers now find it easier to run both organic maize cultivation and non –\norganic maize cultivation. It is a fact that despite organic foods being\nexpensive, the sale of organic food is on the increase, and it is indeed\nprofitable.&nbsp; <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\nfont-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Despite\ncommercial maize farming being a centuries-old industry, this&nbsp;does not in\nany way make the industry over-saturated; commercial maize farmers are\nexploring innovative technology to continue to improve the cultivation,\npreservation, and processing of their product. The fact that there is always a\nready market for maize makes the business highly profitable.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Lastly, it is a common trend to find standard commercial\nmaize farmers run a maize processing plant business alongside their farm. It is\na means of maximizing profit in the business. Additionally, as maize\nis&nbsp;consumed by both humans and livestock, it is ideal to process, package,\nand ship it&nbsp;to other countries of the world.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<strong><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;line-height:107%;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1;mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;\nmso-bidi-language:AR-SA\"><br clear=\"all\" style=\"mso-special-character:line-break;\npage-break-before:always\">\n</span></strong>\n\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;line-height:107%;\nfont-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">&nbsp;</span></strong><strong style=\"background-color: var(--form-control-bg); color: var(--default-font-color); font-size: 0.935rem;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Our Target Market</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">The target markets of those who are the end consumers of\nmaize in any form and who benefit from the business value chain of commercial\nmaize farming is all-encompassing.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Almost every household consumes maize in different forms;\nmaize is sought after in the Nigerian industrial sectors, especially in\nlivestock feeds, breweries, and industrial baking and cooking products and\nconfectionaries. In essence, a commercial maize farmer should be able to sell\nhis or her farm produce to as many people as possible including hotels, grocery\nstores, restaurants, livestock farmers, and production companies that make use\nof maize as raw materials.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">We will ensure that we position our business to attract\nconsumers of maize not just in Nigeria, but also other parts of the world, which\nis why we will be exporting some of our farm produce either in raw or processed\nform to other countries of the world.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Our competitive advantage</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Entrepreneurs gravitate towards industries that are known\nto generate consistent income, which is why commercial farming is such a strong\ninvestment.&nbsp; The world will always need\nfood.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">As a matter of fact, entrepreneurs are encouraged by the\ngovernment to embrace commercial farming. This is so, because part of the\nsuccess of any nation is her ability to cultivate her own food and also export\nfoods to other nations of the world.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Decapolis Maize Farms Project is fully aware that there\nare competitors when it comes to selling commercial farm produce, including\nmaize, all over the globe, which is why we decided to carry out thorough\nresearch, so as to know how to take advantage of the available market in\nNigeria and in other parts of the world.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">We have done our homework and have been able to highlight\nsome factors that will give us a competitive advantage in the marketplace:\neffective and reliable maize farming processes that can help us sell our\nproduce at competitive prices, strong industry network connections, and\nexcellent relationship management.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Another competitive advantage that we are bringing to the\nindustry is the fact that we have designed our business in such a way that we\nwill operate a fully- standardized, commercial maize farm that will also\ninclude a maize processing plant. With this, we will be able to take advantage\nof all the available opportunities within the industry.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">Lastly, our employees will be well taken care of, and\ntheir welfare package will be among the best within our category (start–up\ncommercial maize farms) in the industry, meaning that they will be more than\nwilling to build the business with us, help deliver our set goals and achieve\nall our aims and objectives.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\nmso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-ansi-language:\nEN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA\"><br clear=\"all\" style=\"mso-special-character:line-break;page-break-before:always\">\n</span></b>\n\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\">&nbsp;</span></b><b style=\"background-color: var(--form-control-bg); color: var(--default-font-color); font-size: 0.935rem;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;\ncolor:#C00000\">SALES AND MARKETING STRATEGY</span></b></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:\n11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;mso-themecolor:text1\">Decapolis\nMaize Farms Project is the commercial farming business arm of Decapolis Multi\nConcept Limited. For the purpose of maximizing profits, we have decided to\nexplore all the available opportunities within the industry to achieve our\ncorporate goals and objectives.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif;color:black;\nmso-themecolor:text1\">We do not intend to rely only on the sale of our farm\nproduce to generate income for the business. Below are the sources we intend\nexploring to generate income for the Decapolis Maize Farm Project.<o:p></o:p></span></p><ul type=\"disc\">\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\">Cultivation of\n     various species of maize (both organic and non – organic)<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.5pt;\n     font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,sans-serif\">Standard Food Processing Plant<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachmen