(11, 'Joe Dlevite Farms', '<p>Your Company Profile/Pitch comes here</p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">COMPANY PROFILE</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Company Name: Joe Dlevite Farms (Eat No Wahala)</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Address: Obode Ainu, Oju LGA Benue State, North Central, Nigeria.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Tel: 08169082358</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Email: joedlevitefarms@gmail.com</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">CEO/Founder: Ogbu Joseph Egwu</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Founded: 2018</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Business Sector: Agriculture</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Nature of Business: Yam Production</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">MISSION STATEMENT:&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">To produce organic, sell in line with International Standard, high quality with affordable price.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Respond immediately to the changing needs of our clients.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Achieve complete satisfaction.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Improve our service continuously.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Maintain professional relationship with our dedicated consumers by encouraging ongoing communication to achieve the highest standard of service.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">VISION STATEMENT:&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">To be a leading yam producer in Nigeria in the the next Five (5) years and to be the best organic producer in Africa.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">PITCH</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Title: Ogbu Joseph Egwu, CEO/Managing Director, Joe Dlevite Farms (Eat No Wahala)</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Introduction: \"If we are looking to feed the world for the next 50 years, conventional can do it. But if we\'re looking at feeding the world for the next 1500 years, we must switch over to organic.\" Mark Smallwood.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Problem: I observed that when people eat these days, their healths is deteriorated, Nigeria\'s product got rejected at the International market, worsening the economy of the country due to excessive application of fertilizers/chemicals. Moreso, Nutritional value reduced etc.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Solution: My products are organic without no side effects on the consumers.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Opportunity: organic processes can be easily gotten, technical know-how, available market.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Technology: tractors and other machines for planting are discovered</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Competition: Improved variety of crop. Our product is most stable, best service with highest value, safest. Above all, the product is Organic.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Marketing/Sales: online and offline sales</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Management Team: we have team of Professionals from different academic background on Agriculture.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">IMPACT: Improve health of the consumers, create job opportunity for youths and others, boost economy of the country, contribute to Sustainable Development Goals No.1 No Poverty, No. 2 Zero Hunger. No. 3 Good Health and Well-Being. No. 8 Decent Work and Economic Growth. No. 11 Sustainable Cities and Communities. No. 12 Responsible Consumption and Production.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Financial Projection. Annual Revenue $10,000&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Cost of goods Sold $2,000</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Gross profit $8,000</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Current Status: Existing</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Fund sought: $300,000 Only. It will be used for Logistics purposes. Purchase of&nbsp; (HiAce Hummer Bus, 2 Vehicles) Tractor for ploughing, Recruitment of more Professionals, Consultation services, organic Certifications, exportation training and Certifications and other necessary government requirements to be certified as organic farm.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 12.96px;\">Thanks, as I await your favourable approval please.</span></p>', 7, 18, 70, 70, '2023-03-05 21:54:06', NULL, '2023-03-06 03:54:09', '2023-03-06 03:54:09', NULL),
